reviews.text: Great museum, if your Spanish is not up to reading captions then ask for a guide. They are excellent and free.

Interesting and wide ranging exhibits giving a great overview of signifiers of Bolivia’s culture. 4 stars only because exhibits would be farther reaching if translated to English. More a slight on my lack of Spanish.
Nice museum with masks from last 200 years. The previously were in Sucre.
The visit was amazing, with a free tour guide that tells the Bolivian ethnic history trough themes such as Masks, Feathers, Minerals and etc. Worth the visit.
A great place to get in contact with the several cultures in Bolivia. Their masks exposition is amazing and a must see. Their fabrics collection is great too. Highly recommended
Best textile museum in Bolivia. Impressive indeed, and I loved the shop; I got gifts for everyone and I'm glad to be able to support the weavers too. You must check it out when visiting La Paz!

Lots of great info and examples of regional weaving styles and patterns and a small gift shop. Well worth the 15bs entry fee for a self guided tour. You can fly through the exhibit or take as much time as you want. Photos are allowed.

If you are in La Paz, the museum is a must. The original clothing, history and explanation behind each weaving is clear and educational. A big window into the Andean cultures through their weavings and costumes. I recommend it
Worth the visit even if it is a little off the beaten path. You can take now the Teleférico white line to the Monumento Bush station and make it an adventure!

De paso con unos clientes para tener más idea sobre los textiles que mejor que en el Museo :-) el lugar y la armada del Museo está muy buena la mayoría se ve como que sigue actual y se usa aún, las nuevas generaciones de tejedores de textiles ya casi no manejan nuevas historias o representaciones, que es lo que los textiles nos cuentas de los ancestros y su cultura pero..... felicidades

Mediocre to the fullest. I ordered the Mongolian beef, shrimp fried rice, pork fried rice, and fried wontons. 
1. Fried rice isn’t fried rice at all. It is white rice with chopped veggies. Taste ok but for the price is definitely mediocre. 
2. Mongolian beef tasted like LIVER🤢. 
3. Fried wontons we’re nothing but fried dough. 
4. I paid 287 bs for 2 plates of rice sprinkled with meat, and A piece of beef that tasted nothing like Mongolian beef (tasted like liver), a plate of noodles with shrimp sprinkled on top, and a picture of lemonade, and a side of fried dough, I mean wontons. Lol! That’s $41 USD. 
That’s crazy expensive. 

Waiters are very nice but completely clueless about the menu and Chinese food all together. 
Maybe because they’re Bolivian. 
I asked for soy sauce and he went to find out if they had some 😂. 

SAVE YOUR MONEY!!! Definitely 100% NOT WORTH EVEN TRYING!!!
It is not the nicest place to be but the food is amaizing. Really tasty although not authentic Chinese food.

The place doesn't look like much, but it has been there for decades. I usually order food to go. 
Food itself it's tasty not to greasy.
I always get the rice noodles.

Microwaved food, bits of the meat were ice cold while some other bits were lukewarm. Diarrhea the next day. Makes sense it was empty on a friday evening. If you're thinking of going there, don't. This nothing like traditionnal chinese food. I don't even understand the positive comments. Run away
ok

Not sure why there are so many emotional and contrary comments here. The food at El Sabroso is made with care and fresh ingredients and the price reflects that fairly. I've never encountered negative attitudes in the restaurant. This is good Mexican food and some of the best in Taipei.

Tasty Mexican food in Taipei!!!!!! If you’re from the States like me and crave good Mexican food from time to time, well El Sabroso is the place that will hit the spot. The place is tiny but they serve up good authentic Mexican food.  Hopefully soon they move into a bigger place with more tables and seats for dining in.

Very authentic Mexican in Taipei and probably one of the best in town. Tried their burrito and tacos (only served on Tuesdays) and they were both amazing! Their spicy tomato sauce is also very delicious. Highly recommend it!

100% authentic Mexican food. Not Tex-Mex but Mexican food which is very different.
        The owner and employees are terrific people and LISTEN to what you want! They make great tacos, like in Mexico, where there is meat not just a bunch of onions and vegetables.
        If you don't like the food, you don't like real Mexican food, and your probably use to Taiwanese sweetened, non authentic Mexican food garbage.
     It's right across from the Army hospital with a round sign out side.

One of the best Mexican restaurants I've been to! Quality was put into every aspect from the meal from the tortilla, salsa, horchata and all the ingredients. They didn't take any shortcuts and it resulted in to one amazing burrito!

They do tacos only on Tuesdays and that's until they run out!

The employees are super nice and the menu is available in Chinese and English.

Service 5/5
Quality 5/5
Value 4/5

Good location if you are visiting the tourist area of La Paz.  Very attentive and helpful service.  The whole hotel is now a bit dated, the rooms dark, and bathrooms are tiny.  However, if you are just staying a night they have hot water and are reasonably priced.  They also have double glazing on the windows toward the street so that makes it quite at night.

A very homely boutique hotel in central La Paz. It was once a private home in Spanish Colonial style and has courtyards, guest lounge, breakfast and dining room. The rooms are very comfortable and clean and there are balconies and arched walkways with views of La Paz city which lights up at night time. 
We chose to eat in house each night because the food was good but also, after a day of sightseeing, it was easy to come back to the hotel, shower, relax and eat in, rather than going out again to look for a restaurant.
Highly recommended.

Cozy atmosphere nearby attraction in ancient inca-bolivian style. However, seem like the building renovate from old building so it looks quite old. The room that I stay automatic door lock and its hanger are not good hard to open the door. I didnt try their breakfast because I must to leave around 3:30am but their restaurant's staff works at 4am so they didnt prepare the breakfast box for me. Overall I think quite nice in downtown with their price

A hotel with old school charm and cozy decoration. 

Professional staff who were helpful. There's a transport counter too, to help organise safe taxi trips.

The room was slightly limited in size, as was the bathroom, but clean and fairly warm in its vibes. 

Sound insulation was below average.
Breakfast was continental and nicely provisioned - a fairly good spread including a variety of juices, eggs, and a local potato dish, in addition to the standard cereals and breads.

Definitely a safe bet in La Paz!

great location, very comfy.  Staff is welcoming, accommodating, very polite and helpful. Rooms are spacious and decorated nicely. Beds and pillows very comfortable.  Bathroom is updated and clean. If possible, get a room facing the courtyard as it's very quiet.  We missed breakfast by 15 min but the wait staff was very kind in offering to make us eggs and get us some bread and fruit, we appreciated that a lot. Highly recommend this hotel.
Good appetizer but tallarin saltado too salty
Great food!
Muy buena
Lindo el lugar peruano pequeno y la.comida acceptable precio acceptable
Excelente atención, comida deliciosa y buenos precios.
Awsome place to eat
Muy ricas sus pizzas
El lugar es pequeño, pero el sabor es muy bueno. La masa es delicada y la preparacion tiene ingredientes son frescos y combinaciones dulces y saladas.
Buen lugar
Un lugar para cualquier turista amante de la pizza

We are a family traveling from California and had coffee at this shop on New Year’s Eve afternoon.  We experienced an very disturbing encounter with a white man who harassed my husband in the restroom with racial hatrate raging. The man might be drunk and continued drinking beers after the incidence. Basically he said to my husband that he hated people from US, China and Japan regardless “where you came from”. And he almost began physical attack. Since the man behaved very violent and dangerous, We requested to speak with the store manager and would like to call police to remove the man from the coffee shop. But no action was taken from the store management, not even walked to speak with the man to check on his status. So we had to walk over ourselves to make sure the man was under check by his two companions and don’t want him to follow our son to restroom to continue his crazy behavior...
 The real Bolivia people are hardworking and kind people we have met everywhere. We don’t know where this man came from but we’re very dissatisfied by the coffee shop management.
The only place where find food 24 hrs in La Paz
You can find food at any time, there.... it never closes!!!
Environment ok, quiet, drinks & good, located downtown closeby main public university can be crowded and noisy
Don’t order western food at local places and expect the same taste! We had local basic dishes and they were fine for what we paid.

Un lugar hermoso, increíble la belleza natural , ideal para gozar del silencio, la calma y mucho verde. El mapa no tiene marcado el camino, es un tramo interno desde el pueblo para subir hasta el hostal

Un lugar alucinante, de los mejores en los que me alojé, distinto a todo. Una experiencia de estar en medio del bosque que se potencia en la cabañita en que me hospedé (Jatata), con la sensación de estar lejos de todo (aunque está a pasos del restaurante del hostal y a minutos del pueblo)
Nice

City central, calm coffeehouse atmosphere.  Great original food.  It is by far the best sit-down restaurant in the City limits.  Indoor outdoor seating, with a great panoramic view of the surrounding mountains and city.
Very nice place, Good location, Great view from the terrace. Food was good, will be back to try more of the menu. Prices approximately $6-7 per person for a decent sized main course.
Nice place with great prices. The decor is nice, the menu selection is good, the food is delicious and very reasonably priced.
Very nice place with excellent prices! The patacones with cheese and beans are very tasty.
Cool
Bonito lugar buen ambiente pero mucho condimento en la comida
Muy bueno y buen precio

Muy buen lugar para almorzar, con menús atractivos y con muy buen precio. Además funciona como bar durante la tarde, con ventas de cervezas nacionales y artesanales que las puedes acompañar con pizzas. Se recomienda la visita
Bueno para compartir un momento con los amigos
Great owner and very quirky and lovely ambience inside. It takes you to the middle East. Food was great and the falafels are just amazing

A simpatic place, if you would like to eat something from Morroco, it's not so bad, for my opinion too much salt. The attention is 50%, can be too much better !!! The place is hard to reach, a small restaurant, near the place San Francisco, in La Paz, Bolivia. There's no beer, but wine.
Excellent food, friendly service, cozy, unique and mystic environment

Quaint restaurant with wonderful owner who (if you ask) will provide great conversation in English, French and a number of other places. 
Vegan and vegetarian friendly.
Fabulous palace for delicious food
